node.title: Police shift focus to car in the driveway of Cleo Smith's accused kidnapper
node.description: Detectives investigating the disappearanceÂ of Cleo Smith turn their attention to a car parked at the home where the little girl was found.
node.content:
["The police team investigating the abduction of four-year-old Cleo Smith have shifted their focus to a car parked in the driveway of her alleged kidnapper.", "Forensics officers have remained at the Carnarvon home of Terence Kelly\u00a0ever since Cleo was rescued in the early hours of Wednesday morning after she had been missing for 18 days.\u00a0", "One of the key people involved in Cleo's rescue, Detective Senior Sergeant Cameron Blaine, returned to the property on Tuesday to speak with officers at the scene.\u00a0", "", "
Detective Senior Sergeant Cameron Blaine, who was one of the officers involved in Cleo's rescue, is continuing the investigation into her abduction.(ABC News: Evelyn Manfield)
", "He would not comment on the investigation.\u00a0", "On Monday, he said the investigation was going well and detectives would stay in town until at least the end of the week as they tried to ascertain whether more than one person could have been involved in the four-year-old's alleged abduction from her family's tent at the Blowholes campsite.", "Forensic officers\u00a0examining the car were dressed in blue PPE, gloves and were wearing face masks.", "", "
Cleo Smith and her mother Ellie at Carnarvon police station.(ABC News: Evelyn Manfield)
", "Meanwhile, Cleo Smith, her mother Ellie Smith and stepfather Jake Gliddon briefly\u00a0visited Carnarvon Police Station."]
